DetailedDescription: A Vermin Talisman allows you to summon a swarm of rats at the house of a target player.
It will take a night for the rats to arrive.
Once they have arrived, the swarm will affect the target and any player visiting the target.
Any player affected by the swarm will be role and item blocked and also be seen visiting one of the targets neighbours as they run away.
The swarm will move at the end of each night to a random player up to two houses away from their current location.
If the swarm move to a player that is killed on the same night, they will disperse.
If the swarm are currently active, you may use the talisman again to disperse them and then re-summon them on a subsequent night.

Description: An Iron Collar can save you from a single lynch.
The Essence of the Ancient One will corrupt someone's speech.
The Essence of the Ancient One will corrupt someone's speech.
The Essence of the Ancient One will corrupt someone's speech.

A Fela Rune allows you to make a player invisible for one night, hiding them from Stalker and Harlot checks. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.
A Potion of Cleansing can be used to remove all negative effects applied to a player, like Poison
A Wolf Pelt will protect you from one night kill, but it will make you appear as a Werewolf to the Seer

The Tumultum is an ancient device that looks like a brass instrument. Once per game it can be blown. It will disrupt the sleep of everyone in the village - giving everyone a random extra visit and the power of an insomniac that night.
A Potion of Clarity allows you to find out a player's alignment

The Demonic Eye is a glowing green jewel. Those that hold it feel an immediate compulsion to drive it into their eye socket, where it takes on the form of a human eye with a deep green iris. The Eye grants them the ability to see those who are blighted, and the power remove blight from one player per night.
A Hell Helm allows you to listen to any messages a player sends on the following night

An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

DetailedDescription: A Vermin Talisman allows you to summon a swarm of rats at the house of a target player.
It will take a night for the rats to arrive.
Once they have arrived, the swarm will affect the target and any player visiting the target.
Any player affected by the swarm will be role and item blocked and also be seen visiting one of the targets neighbours as they run away.
The swarm will move at the end of each night to a random player up to two houses away from their current location.
If the swarm move to a player that is killed on the same night, they will disperse.
If the swarm are currently active, you may use the talisman again to disperse them and then re-summon them on a subsequent night.

Description: An Iron Collar can save you from a single lynch.
The Essence of the Ancient One will corrupt someone's speech.
The Essence of the Ancient One will corrupt someone's speech.
The Essence of the Ancient One will corrupt someone's speech.

A Fela Rune allows you to make a player invisible for one night, hiding them from Stalker and Harlot checks. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.
A Potion of Cleansing can be used to remove all negative effects applied to a player, like Poison
A Wolf Pelt will protect you from one night kill, but it will make you appear as a Werewolf to the Seer
A Potion of Clarity allows you to find out a player's alignment

The Demonic Eye is a glowing green jewel. Those that hold it feel an immediate compulsion to drive it into their eye socket, where it takes on the form of a human eye with a deep green iris. The Eye grants them the ability to see those who are blighted, and the power remove blight from one player per night.
A Hell Helm allows you to listen to any messages a player sends on the following night

An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

DetailedDescription: A Vermin Talisman allows you to summon a swarm of rats at the house of a target player.
It will take a night for the rats to arrive.
Once they have arrived, the swarm will affect the target and any player visiting the target.
Any player affected by the swarm will be role and item blocked and also be seen visiting one of the targets neighbours as they run away.
The swarm will move at the end of each night to a random player up to two houses away from their current location.
If the swarm move to a player that is killed on the same night, they will disperse.
If the swarm are currently active, you may use the talisman again to disperse them and then re-summon them on a subsequent night.

Description: The Essence of the Ancient One will corrupt someone's speech.

A Fela Rune allows you to make a player invisible for one night, hiding them from Stalker and Harlot checks. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.
The Essence of the Ancient One will corrupt someone's speech.
The Essence of the Ancient One will corrupt someone's speech.
A Wolf Pelt will protect you from one night kill, but it will make you appear as a Werewolf to the Seer

The Eye grants them the ability to see those who are blighted, and the power remove blight from one player per night.
A Hell Helm allows you to listen to any messages a player sends on the following night

An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. DetailedDescription: A Vermin Talisman allows you to summon a swarm of rats at the house of a target player.
It will take a night for the rats to arrive.
Once they have arrived, the swarm will affect the target and any player visiting the target.
Any player affected by the swarm will be role and item blocked and also be seen visiting one of the targets neighbours as they run away.
The swarm will move at the end of each night to a random player up to two houses away from their current location.
If the swarm move to a player that is killed on the same night, they will disperse.
If the swarm are currently active, you may use the talisman again to disperse them and then re-summon them on a subsequent night.

Description: The Essence of the Ancient One will corrupt someone's speech.

A Fela Rune allows you to make a player invisible for one night, hiding them from Stalker and Harlot checks. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.
A Wolf Pelt will protect you from one night kill, but it will make you appear as a Werewolf to the Seer

The Demonic Eye is a glowing green jewel. Those that hold it feel an immediate compulsion to drive it into their eye socket, where it takes on the form of a human eye with a deep green iris. The Eye grants them the ability to see those who are blighted, and the power remove blight from one player per night.
A Hell Helm allows you to listen to any messages a player sends on the following night

An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

DetailedDescription: A Vermin Talisman allows you to summon a swarm of rats at the house of a target player.
It will take a night for the rats to arrive.
Once they have arrived, the swarm will affect the target and any player visiting the target.
Any player affected by the swarm will be role and item blocked and also be seen visiting one of the targets neighbours as they run away.
The swarm will move at the end of each night to a random player up to two houses away from their current location.
If the swarm move to a player that is killed on the same night, they will disperse.
If the swarm are currently active, you may use the talisman again to disperse them and then re-summon them on a subsequent night.

Description: A Fela Rune allows you to make a player invisible for one night, hiding them from Stalker and Harlot checks. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.
A Wolf Pelt will protect you from one night kill, but it will make you appear as a Werewolf to the Seer

The Demonic Eye is a glowing green jewel. Those that hold it feel an immediate compulsion to drive it into their eye socket, where it takes on the form of a human eye with a deep green iris. The Eye grants them the ability to see those who are blighted, and the power remove blight from one player per night.
A Hell Helm allows you to listen to any messages a player sends on the following night

An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

DetailedDescription: A Vermin Talisman allows you to summon a swarm of rats at the house of a target player.
It will take a night for the rats to arrive.
Once they have arrived, the swarm will affect the target and any player visiting the target.
Any player affected by the swarm will be role and item blocked and also be seen visiting one of the targets neighbours as they run away.
The swarm will move at the end of each night to a random player up to two houses away from their current location.
If the swarm move to a player that is killed on the same night, they will disperse.
If the swarm are currently active, you may use the talisman again to disperse them and then re-summon them on a subsequent night.

Description: A Fela Rune allows you to make a player invisible for one night, hiding them from Stalker and Harlot checks. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

The Demonic Eye is a glowing green jewel. Those that hold it feel an immediate compulsion to drive it into their eye socket, where it takes on the form of a human eye with a deep green iris. The Eye grants them the ability to see those who are blighted, and the power remove blight from one player per night.
A Hell Helm allows you to listen to any messages a player sends on the following night

An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.
A Wolf Pelt will protect you from one night kill, but it will make you appear as a Werewolf to the Seer

Any player affected by the swarm will be role and item blocked and also be seen visiting one of the targets neighbours as they run away.
The swarm will move at the end of each night to a random player up to two houses away from their current location.
If the swarm move to a player that is killed on the same night, they will disperse.
If the swarm are currently active, you may use the talisman again to disperse them and then re-summon them on a subsequent night.

Description: The Demonic Eye is a glowing green jewel. Those that hold it feel an immediate compulsion to drive it into their eye socket, where it takes on the form of a human eye with a deep green iris. The Eye grants them the ability to see those who are blighted, and the power remove blight from one player per night.

An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

A Fela Rune allows you to make a player invisible for one night, hiding them from Stalker and Harlot checks. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

DetailedDescription: A Vermin Talisman allows you to summon a swarm of rats at the house of a target player.
It will take a night for the rats to arrive.
Once they have arrived, the swarm will affect the target and any player visiting the target.
Any player affected by the swarm will be role and item blocked and also be seen visiting one of the targets neighbours as they run away.
The swarm will move at the end of each night to a random player up to two houses away from their current location.
If the swarm move to a player that is killed on the same night, they will disperse.
If the swarm are currently active, you may use the talisman again to disperse them and then re-summon them on a subsequent night.

Description: The Demonic Eye is a glowing green jewel. Those that hold it feel an immediate compulsion to drive it into their eye socket, where it takes on the form of a human eye with a deep green iris. The Eye grants them the ability to see those who are blighted, and the power remove blight from one player per night.

An Avleda Rune allows you redirect all visits to a target player to yourself for one night. This includes item usage and item transfers. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

A Fela Rune allows you to make a player invisible for one night, hiding them from Stalker and Harlot checks. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.
A Hell Helm allows you to listen to any messages a player sends on the following night
A Wolf Pelt will protect you from one night kill, but it will make you appear as a Werewolf to the Seer
